{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed AI Monitor Program makes extensive use of machine learning and AI systems to enhance road safety.",
    "An activity recognition system based on deep CNNs successfully identifies seven common driver activities.",
    "Four of these activities are classified as normal driving tasks and the rest as distractions, achieving an impressive 91.4 percent accuracy rate.",
    "Another approach uses CNN to develop a real-time warning system for driver distraction detection.",
    "A unique approach inhabits the use of cellular neural networks and electrostatic sensors on the steering wheel for real-time stress level monitoring, improving detection accuracy by up to 92 percent [136][137][138].Understanding driving behaviors like car-following, lane-changing, and risky driving can be improved using sensor data, onboard vehicle computer data, and feature extraction methods."
  ]
}